SW group shares one UBR10K, which is equipped with two PRE2:

  SYS13_U10K_PRE_1_  spaulsen     172.22.24.35     2013  group-jimhuang
  SYS13_U10K_PRE_2_  spaulsen     172.22.24.35     2014  group-jimhuang

To reload, first do "no shut" on fa0/0/0, then reload the active PRE.
After the active PRE is up, need to do a shut on fa0/0/0. 

Also needs to shut gi4/0/0.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
To boot to ROMMON:

Make sure there is no such configuration:
(otherwise will boot from disk0:)
  boot system disk0:ubr10k-k9p6u2-mz

In IOS: 
  conf t
  config-register

To download images from tftp server:
  connect Fast Ethernet port on PRE to one of the lab net drop (orange)
  config fa0/0/0 with the correct IP address and net mask

--------------------------------------------------------------------

The ubr10k is boot up in this sequence:

- ROMMON
- Boot code
- Full IOS code

In the boot image, need to set the default gateway
so it can reach the tftp server:

conf t
ip default-gateway 2.9.0.1

-------------------------------------------------------------

To boot up an image from TFTP server from ROMMON:

boot ytse/<image_name>

-------------------------------------------------------------
Image building:

In sys/obj-4k-cr10k2-rp (for PRE2)
    make ubr10k2-p6-mz
    make ubr10k2-k8p6-mz (with BPI)

In sys/obj-4k-cr10-rp (for PRE1)
    make ubr10k-p6-mz
                                  
